1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. g3 d5 5. Bg2 O-O 6. Nf3 dxc4 7. O-O Nc6 8. e3
Rb8 9. Qe2 b5 10. Rd1 Nd5 11. Bd2 Be7 $1 12. Ne4 {I dont like this move as now
knight stays on the way of the central pawns.} (12. e4 Ndb4 13. d5 exd5 14.
exd5 Nxd5 $1 15. Ne1 Nd4 16. Qe5 Nb6 $1 $13) 12... Ba6 13. b3 (13. Nc5 $6 Bxc5
14. dxc5 Qe7 15. Nd4 Nxd4 16. exd4 Qd7) 13... Qc8 $1 {I like this move - the
queen not only escapes from the opposition, but at the same time protects the
bishop on "a6".} (13... f5 $6 14. Nc5 Bxc5 15. dxc5 Qf6 (15... c3 16. Be1) 16.
e4 fxe4 17. Qxe4) 14. Be1 h6 (14... c3 {was possible, but Graf prepares a
devilish trap}) 15. a4 $6 {This move looks like White's only active idea.} c3
$1 {It seems that Black is already winning.} 16. Bf1 (16. b4 bxa4 17. Qc2 Ncxb4
18. Qxa4 Bb5) 16... bxa4 $1 {Now White realized that all was a trap, but it is
already too late.} 17. Qxa6 Qxa6 18. Bxa6 c2 19. bxa4 (19. Rdc1 axb3) 19...
cxd1=Q 20. Rxd1 Rb2 21. Rc1 Ncb4 22. Bf1 Rc2 23. Rb1 Ra2 24. Nc5 Bxc5 25. dxc5
Nc2 26. Bd2 Rxa4 27. e4 Nf6 28. Bd3 Nd4 29. Ne1 Nd7 30. c6 Ne5 31. Bf4 Nxd3 32.
Nxd3 Nxc6 33. Rc1 Nd4 0-1

