) 13. e3 Qf6 14. exd4 Nxd4 15. Nxd4 Qxd4 16. Rac1 Qxc4 17. Qxc3 Qxc3 18. Rxc3
Rd8 19. Rfc1 Rb8 20. Rc7 g6 21. f4 a6 22. Bf3 Bd7 23. Rxb7 Bb5 $11) ({The move
} 11. Qd3 {is very well met by} Qd5 $1 $146 {Black's idea is to support the
"d4" pawn by means of e5 when white queen on "d3" is rather badly placed.} (
11... Re8 12. Nfe5 Nxe5 13. Nxe5 Qd6 14. f4 {gave White pressure in Mareco,S
-Slipak,S  Saenz Pena ARG, 2014.}) 12. b4 (12. Rfd1 e5 $1) (12. Rac1 e5 13. Ng5
Qc5 14. b4 Qe7 15. b5 Nd8 16. f4 exf4 17. Rxf4 Ne6 18. Nxe6 Bxe6 19. Rxd4 Rac8
$36) 12... e5 (12... Qh5 $6 13. Nxd4 Rd8 14. Bxc6 bxc6 15. Qc3) 13. Ng5 Qb5 14.
Rfc1 h6 15. Ne4 Nxe4 16. Bxe4 {and now the safest for Black is} Nd8 (16... Bd7
17. Rab1 $36) (16... f5 17. Bxc6 bxc6 18. a4 Qd5 19. Na5 Bd7 20. Rc5 Qe4 21.
Qc4+ Kh8 22. Nxc6 Bxc6 23. Rxc6 f4 24. b5 Qf5 $132) 17. a4 Qe8 18. e3 f5 19.
