Bd7 12. Rc1 Rc8 13. Qd2 Nxe5 14. Nxe5 Qb6) 11... a5 $1 {I think for Black is
better to prevent b4.} (11... Re8 12. b4 $1 (12. Nfe5 Nxe5 13. Nxe5 Qb6 14. Qc2
Nd7 $1) 12... a6 (12... e5 {is interesting attempt to solve the problems
immediately.} 13. b5 Na5 14. Ncxe5 $1 (14. Nfxe5 Nxc4 15. Nxc4 Bg4 $11 16. Re1
